	<Title>
		Blood pressure tip: Watch your weight
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Blood pressure often increases as weight increases. In general, the more weight you lose, the lower your blood pressure. If you&apos;re overweight, losing even 10 pounds can make a big difference. Work with your doctor to determine your target weight and the best way to achieve it.&lt;/p&gt;
